@peternocturnal @Sharkyl pretty much just like strikes in baseball, if you aren't making progress downfield then the advantage goes to the other team offensively.
@peternocturnal @Sharkyl any tldr, a down where you touch the ball behind the other teams goal line is a touch down, simple as that, a down in which you touch.

@peternocturnal @Sharkyl with this rule, if you try to run down the clock you will eventually find that you have to give the ball up and switch to defense, the offensive team must be actively moving down field towards the other teams goal and cant do any shenanigans to prolong plays

@peternocturnal @Sharkyl this was to solve a problem with the way people played american rules football, namely, teams would get a lead then start stalling out the game as much as they can to ensure the other team has no chance to score. it made early american football in the 19th century a slog.

@peternocturnal @Sharkyl exactly, also all plays being carried out are downs, a down is just a measurement of a period of play, the point from which the ball is in play until someone gets tackled or goes out of bounds is a single down.

everyone gets 4 downs per 10 yards in american football.
Famously @Sharkyl this was a technique used in early football games to win, get in the lead then stall the game out, it was very boring to watch

if after 4 downs you fail to pass the 1st down line, you have to give the ball back to the other team and switch to defense.

this is so you can't just run the timer down when you're winning you have to progress down the field or give the other team a chance to score.

In American Football the downs are used to measure when the team who has the ball has to give it back to the other team, every team gets 4 downs or 4 plays to get the ball past the current "First Down Line" which if passed will reset the current down to 1st down.

a down is the period of time after a play starts before a tackle wherein the game is being played and players run around/throw the ball. 

a -touch- down, is a down during which the team with the ball ~touches~ it on the ground behind the other teams goal line. hence. touch down. https://t.co/RLDbOTe9Ym
